ariables, with the others held constant. Partial derivatives are used in <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector_calculus" title=3D"Vector cal=
culus">vector calculus</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dif=
ferential_geometry" title=3D"Differential geometry">differential geometry</=
a>. As with ordinary derivatives, multiple notations exist: the partial der=
ivative of a function <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inli=
ne"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"di=
