<p>The concept of a derivative can be extended to many other settings. The =
common thread is that the derivative of a function at a point serves as a <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_approximation" title=3D"Line=
ar approximation">linear approximation</a> of the function at that point.
</p>
